      <div class="SOTTO_PARA"><a name="DUC6a1af2b82aaa10058bbdf20939ae18d2"></a>Refitting the oil sump guard
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e962"> </a>Do vibration damper (18) finger tight on oil sump, on the longer threaded side.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e964"> </a>Refit the brackets (15) and (16) and respectively start the screws (2) and (17).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e966"> </a>Tighten the screw (2) to a torque of 5 Nm ± 10% and the screw (17) to a torque of 24 Nm ± 10%.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e968"> </a>Make sure that bracket (15) fits clip (19) and bracket (16) fits clip (20).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_5_010203064.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_5_010303065.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e975"> </a>Install clips (19), vibration dampers (13) and (5) and spacer (4) to lower belly pan (10).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e977"> </a>Refit the lower belly pan (10), start (without tightening) nut (12), screws (11) and screw (2) on the LH side, positioning
            hose guide(9) under the latter.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e979"> </a>Tighten nut (12) and screws (11) to a torque of 24 Nm ± 10%.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e981"> </a>Tighten screw (2) to a torque of 5 Nm ± 10%. Fit tank breather/drain hoses, expansion tank hose and airbox drain pipe inside
            hose guide (9).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/note.jpg">Note
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e984"> </a>Length after guide must be more or less the same for all hoses and pipes.
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_5_010403066.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_5_010503067.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e991"> </a>Install rubber blocks (5) and spacers (4) on RH belly pan (7) .
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e993"> </a>Refit RH belly pan (7), start and tighten the screws (2) and (3) to a torque of 5 Nm ± 10%.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_5_009703059.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e998"> </a>When fitting the RH belly pan, make sure not to squeeze cable (21) between belly pan and engine bracket (22).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_5_010603068.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e1004"> </a>Install rubber blocks (5) and spacers (4) on LH belly pan (1) .
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e1006"> </a>Refit the LH belly pan (1), start screws (2), using washer (6) under front screw, and start screw (3).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e1008"> </a>Tighten the screws (2) and (3) to a torque of 5 Nm ± 10%.
         </div>
      </div>
